I'll be fine.

1021
01:01:54,411 --> 01:01:56,881
How could you talk
to me like that in front
of our guests?

1022
01:01:56,914 --> 01:01:57,948
It was hard not to.

1023
01:01:57,982 --> 01:01:59,016
Hanging on her every word.

1024
01:01:59,049 --> 01:02:01,285
I enjoyed her enthusiasm.

1025
01:02:01,318 --> 01:02:02,853
Seeing things the way
she sees them with...

1026
01:02:02,887 --> 01:02:05,455
You're acting like
a smitten school boy, not
a scientist. It's ridiculous.

1027
01:02:05,489 --> 01:02:08,158
-I'm proud of her.
-Proud?

1028
01:02:08,192 --> 01:02:10,828
I've seen you look at her
in ways I've only
dreamed about.

1029
01:02:10,861 --> 01:02:12,229
I don't think
you even realize it.

1030
01:02:12,262 --> 01:02:15,199
I am looking at who she is!

1031
01:02:15,232 --> 01:02:17,467
What she is. She's just there,
no strings.

1032
01:02:17,501 --> 01:02:19,136
Pure and simple.

1033
01:02:19,169 --> 01:02:20,037
Do you hear
what you're saying?

1034
01:02:20,070 --> 01:02:22,873
I have never, ever, ever
known that before.

1035
01:02:22,907 --> 01:02:24,441
Not with you,
not with my colleagues,

1036
01:02:24,474 --> 01:02:26,877
and certainly,
certainly never
with my father.

1037
01:02:26,911 --> 01:02:28,378
-(ZIPPING)
-I need some time to think.

1038
01:02:28,412 --> 01:02:30,114
Oh, really?

1039
01:02:30,147 --> 01:02:31,548
And you better
sort things out too.

1040
01:02:31,581 --> 01:02:32,817
What does that mean?

1041
01:02:32,850 --> 01:02:34,251
It means I'm leaving.

1042
01:02:37,521 --> 01:02:40,524
(SIGHS) Are you in love
with her mind?
Is that what it is?

1043
01:02:40,557 --> 01:02:43,127
Anybody can be a genius.
We've proven that, haven't we?

1044
01:02:43,160 --> 01:02:45,796
Just add our formula and stir.

1045
01:02:53,938 --> 01:02:55,272
(CLOCK CHIMING)

1046
01:03:09,086 --> 01:03:10,087
DINA: Mitch...

1047
01:03:11,321 --> 01:03:12,156
I...

1048
01:03:13,490 --> 01:03:14,825
I, uh,

1049
01:03:14,859 --> 01:03:15,860
got some milk.

1050
01:03:34,945 --> 01:03:36,013
I...

1051
01:03:37,581 --> 01:03:38,983
Love you.

1052
01:03:40,650 --> 01:03:41,952
So...

1053
01:03:47,557 --> 01:03:49,026
I know

1054
01:03:51,328 --> 01:03:52,562
in here.

1055
01:04:15,452 --> 01:04:16,453
(DOOR SHUTS)

1056
01:04:18,322 --> 01:04:19,523
(WHISPERS) I love you too.

1057
01:04:36,573 --> 01:04:37,942
-Oh!
-(SHRIEKING)

1058
01:04:45,315 --> 01:04:47,051
How did you get out?

1059
01:04:47,084 --> 01:04:48,252
I changed the combination.

1060
01:04:49,386 --> 01:04:51,021
(SHRIEKING)

1061
01:04:51,055 --> 01:04:52,289
What's the matter
with you two?

1062
01:04:53,523 --> 01:04:55,225
Hey! Come here. Come here!

1063
01:04:55,259 --> 01:04:57,061
(CONTINUES SHRIEKING)

1064
01:04:58,095 --> 01:04:59,229
Hey!

1065
01:05:02,099 --> 01:05:04,134
Stop it! Come here!

1066
01:05:05,235 --> 01:05:06,636
Come on, yeah.

1067
01:05:06,670 --> 01:05:07,671
That's a good girl.

1068
01:05:07,704 --> 01:05:09,206
Come here.

1069
01:05:11,741 --> 01:05:14,344
That's it, come on. That's it.

1070
01:05:14,378 --> 01:05:16,113
Come on, yeah. Stay!

1071
01:05:19,283 --> 01:05:21,118
-(MONKEY PANTING)
-(SIGHS)

1072
01:05:21,151 --> 01:05:22,987
You aren't sleeping. Why?

1073
01:05:23,653 --> 01:05:25,222
(SHRIEKING)

1074
01:05:26,456 --> 01:05:28,558
Damn, you picked a fine
time to have a reaction.

1075
01:05:30,594 --> 01:05:32,429
I have to take you off
the formula.

1076
01:05:54,484 --> 01:05:55,319
Linda.

1077
01:06:00,524 --> 01:06:02,092
I'm sorry.

1078
01:06:02,792 --> 01:06:04,995
Seven cc's. Reaction...

1079
01:06:06,363 --> 01:06:07,297
"None."

1080
01:06:26,316 --> 01:06:27,984
Leonard,

1081
01:06:28,018 --> 01:06:31,655
if you lowered the temperature
and added a 17% solution of
beta-Mercaptoethanol...

1082
01:06:31,688 --> 01:06:33,590
It's fine. Study.

1083
01:06:33,623 --> 01:06:37,261
Or better yet,
first extract the DNA with,
uh, a phenol chloroform.

1084
01:06:37,294 --> 01:06:38,595
-It's fine. (SIGHS)
-You'd get a better yield.

1085
01:06:40,297 --> 01:06:43,367
With the DNA isolation,
you get less digestion.

1086
01:06:43,400 --> 01:06:44,434
Dina.

1087
01:06:44,468 --> 01:06:46,436
I've done this 1,000 times.

1088
01:06:46,470 --> 01:06:48,372
DINA: I just read it
yesterday in

1089
01:06:48,405 --> 01:06:52,276
volume 11, page 139.

1090
01:06:52,309 --> 01:06:54,010
-Let me do my job.
-One second.

1091
01:06:54,811 --> 01:06:56,580
Never mind. I'm finished.

1092
01:07:01,151 --> 01:07:03,220
It's late. I'm going home.

1093
01:07:10,794 --> 01:07:12,329
You should too.

1094
01:07:12,362 --> 01:07:14,098
I can't.
I have some studying to do.

1095
01:07:14,131 --> 01:07:14,931
Get some rest.

1096
01:07:18,802 --> 01:07:20,170
Here it is. Leonard!

1097
01:07:24,241 --> 01:07:25,275
TEACHER: (ON TAPE)
 Where is the library?

1098
01:07:25,309 --> 01:07:27,677
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1099
01:07:28,478 --> 01:07:31,248
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1100
01:07:31,848 --> 01:07:33,483
TEACHER: The library is there.

1101
01:07:33,517 --> 01:07:35,552
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1102
01:07:35,585 --> 01:07:36,653
Come on, come on.

1103
01:07:36,686 --> 01:07:39,556
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1104
01:07:39,589 --> 01:07:42,426
-Are you going there now? 
 -(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1105
01:07:42,459 --> 01:07:46,630
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1106
01:07:46,663 --> 01:07:48,765
-Yes, I have to look 
 for a book. 
-DINA: Oui.

1107
01:07:48,798 --> 01:07:51,601
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1108
01:07:51,635 --> 01:07:52,836
Come on. (SIGHS)

1109
01:07:53,670 --> 01:07:57,307
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1110
01:07:57,341 --> 01:07:58,408
Merde.

1111
01:07:59,409 --> 01:08:00,744
(TAPE REWINDING)

1112
01:08:00,777 --> 01:08:02,512
(VOICE DISTORTING)

1113
01:08:02,546 --> 01:08:03,747
(SIGHS)

1114
01:08:05,449 --> 01:08:06,250
Damn.

1115
01:08:08,752 --> 01:08:10,120
(MONKEY VOCALIZING SOFTLY)

1116
01:08:31,208 --> 01:08:33,210
MAN: (CHANTING)
What's at stake?

1117
01:08:33,243 --> 01:08:34,578
Join us.

1118
01:08:34,611 --> 01:08:36,380
What's at stake?

1119
01:08:36,813 --> 01:08:38,382
What's at stake?

1120
01:08:38,415 --> 01:08:40,584
-Come on, join us.
-ALL: What's at stake?

1121
01:08:40,617 --> 01:08:42,919
What's at stake?

1122
01:08:42,952 --> 01:08:46,790
What's at stake? Dina Blake.

1123
01:08:46,823 --> 01:08:50,627
What's at stake? Dina Blake.

1124
01:08:50,660 --> 01:08:54,564
What's at stake? Dina Blake.

1125
01:08:54,598 --> 01:08:58,202
What's at stake? Dina Blake.

1126
01:08:58,768 --> 01:09:00,304
You look tired.

1127
01:09:00,737 --> 01:09:02,639
Can't stop studying.

1128
01:09:02,672 --> 01:09:03,873
You should slow down a little.

1129
01:09:03,907 --> 01:09:06,210
Can't. Just not enough
hours in the day.

1130
01:09:06,243 --> 01:09:07,844
You need to relax.

1131
01:09:07,877 --> 01:09:09,779
Don't have the time.
The fundraiser's coming up.

1132
01:09:10,547 --> 01:09:11,715
What fundraiser?

1133
01:09:11,748 --> 01:09:15,185
I have to make a speech and
raise money.

1134
01:09:15,219 --> 01:09:16,653
No, they've got you
on a treadmill.

1135
01:09:16,686 --> 01:09:17,787
No, they need me.

1136
01:09:17,821 --> 01:09:20,490
You're proof
their experiment worked.
They're using you.

1137
01:09:20,524 --> 01:09:22,859
No, they're not.
I have to be prepared.
That's all.

1138
01:09:22,892 --> 01:09:24,661
ALL: Dina! Dina! Dina!

1139
01:09:24,694 --> 01:09:26,796
Come see our dance!

1140
01:09:26,830 --> 01:09:28,965
-I really don't...
-We copied it off
a music video.

1141
01:09:28,998 --> 01:09:30,634
-Not right now, all right?
-Can we show you?

1142
01:09:30,667 --> 01:09:31,901
No! I'm talking to Andy.

1143
01:09:33,370 --> 01:09:34,404
Sorry.

1144
01:09:34,938 --> 01:09:36,440
Let's go.

1145
01:09:36,473 --> 01:09:37,274
Come on, guys.

1146
01:09:41,478 --> 01:09:42,512
That's not like you.

1147
01:09:45,515 --> 01:09:46,883
Don't lecture me.

1148
01:09:46,916 --> 01:09:48,752
-You came here to talk.
You don't want to listen?
-Andy drop it.

1149
01:09:48,785 --> 01:09:50,654
No, you can't even see it,
can you?

1150
01:09:50,687 --> 01:09:52,822
-You and Svengali,
so high and mighty...
-Don't criticize Mitch.

1151
01:09:52,856 --> 01:09:54,824
They gave you a brain.
You're not using it.

1152
01:09:54,858 --> 01:09:56,526
I'm going back
to the Institute.

1153
01:09:58,362 --> 01:09:59,663
ANDY: You even know
why you're doing this?

1154
01:09:59,696 --> 01:10:01,231
DINA: I'm doing it
because I love it.

1155
01:10:01,265 --> 01:10:02,866
You're doing it
because you love him!

1156
01:10:03,367 --> 01:10:05,269
(SIGHS)

1157
01:10:05,302 --> 01:10:07,471
I'm doing it because
I'm ambitious,

1158
01:10:07,504 --> 01:10:09,706
something you wouldn't
understand.

1159
01:10:14,511 --> 01:10:16,280
(SYMPHONY PLAYING)

1160
01:10:45,575 --> 01:10:47,944
My, my, my. There's just
no end to your talent,

1161
01:10:47,977 --> 01:10:49,279
is there?

1162
01:10:49,313 --> 01:10:50,614
You scared me.

1163
01:10:53,517 --> 01:10:55,419
The Van Gogh?

1164
01:10:55,452 --> 01:10:56,853
It's Mitch's favorite.

1165
01:10:57,754 --> 01:10:59,489
And a heart of gold, too.

1166
01:10:59,523 --> 01:11:02,292
You're just too good
to be true.

1167
01:11:02,326 --> 01:11:04,328
Let me give you
a little word of advice.

1168
01:11:04,361 --> 01:11:07,297
I wouldn't be wasting my time
on painting if I were you.

1169
01:11:07,331 --> 01:11:09,699
I'd be planning
for my future.

1170
01:11:09,733 --> 01:11:11,368
What does that mean?

1171
01:11:11,401 --> 01:11:13,503
You're so naive.

1172
01:11:13,537 --> 01:11:17,407
You think you just took
the world by storm,
don't you?

1173
01:11:17,441 --> 01:11:19,343
You're only a clinical
curiosity, honey.

1174
01:11:19,376 --> 01:11:21,044
Mitch doesn't really care
about you.

1175
01:11:21,077 --> 01:11:22,712
He's created you in his
own image.

1176
01:11:23,880 --> 01:11:26,883
He's in love with himself.

1177
01:11:26,916 --> 01:11:29,319
Just perform your little
tricks at the presentation.

1178
01:11:29,353 --> 01:11:30,820
That's all we need from you.

1179
01:11:30,854 --> 01:11:32,989
Let Mitch show you off.

1180
01:11:33,022 --> 01:11:34,558
Then you can go back
to your little world.

1181
01:11:41,598 --> 01:11:43,400
I thought you should see this.

1182
01:11:43,433 --> 01:11:45,835
It's from Decauer
and some of the others.

1183
01:11:45,869 --> 01:11:47,404
They're concerned about Dina.

1184
01:11:47,437 --> 01:11:49,539
She's edgy,
she's over-tired...

1185
01:11:49,573 --> 01:11:51,708
Ah, well, everybody's edgy.
We all are before
the presentation.

1186
01:11:51,741 --> 01:11:53,042
-It's... It's normal.
-No.

1187
01:11:53,076 --> 01:11:54,378
Don't explain this away.

1188
01:11:56,079 --> 01:11:58,848
Dina looks to you
for approval,

1189
01:11:58,882 --> 01:12:01,785
for reassurance,
for her identity.

1190
01:12:01,818 --> 01:12:03,820
She'll do anything for you.

1191
01:12:03,853 --> 01:12:06,690
Let her leave and get on
with her life.

1192
01:12:06,723 --> 01:12:08,358
I'll talk to her.

1193
01:12:09,793 --> 01:12:10,994
After the presentation.

1194
01:12:13,930 --> 01:12:15,999
This isn't about winning
prizes anymore.

1195
01:12:17,667 --> 01:12:18,868
(SIGHS)

1196
01:12:24,974 --> 01:12:27,043
LINDA: Hang in there, girls.

1197
01:12:27,076 --> 01:12:29,513
Just for a few more days.

1198
01:12:29,546 --> 01:12:31,781
Then the fundraiser
will be over.

1199
01:12:31,815 --> 01:12:33,517
They'll renew our grant,

1200
01:12:35,519 --> 01:12:36,853
and Dina can go away.

1201
01:12:42,626 --> 01:12:44,394
(MUSIC PLAYING)

1202
01:12:52,769 --> 01:12:53,870
(SIGHS)

1203
01:12:53,903 --> 01:12:55,038
(MONKEY SHRIEKING)

1204
01:13:16,760 --> 01:13:19,062
MAN: Ladies and gentlemen, 
 it is with great pleasure

1205
01:13:19,095 --> 01:13:22,198
that I introduce to you 
 our hosts for this evening,

1206
01:13:22,231 --> 01:13:25,001
Dr. Mitch Conlon 
 and Dr. Linda Ryan.

1207
01:13:25,034 --> 01:13:26,636
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

1208
01:13:28,037 --> 01:13:30,139
Good evening, 
 ladies and gentlemen.

1209
01:13:30,173 --> 01:13:32,041
On behalf of 
 the Conlon Institute,

1210
01:13:32,075 --> 01:13:33,677
I would like to welcome you 
 and thank you

1211
01:13:33,710 --> 01:13:36,045
for your continuing 
 and enthusiastic support

1212
01:13:36,079 --> 01:13:37,681
of our work here.

1213
01:13:37,714 --> 01:13:39,115
Mitch, why are you hiding?

1214
01:13:39,148 --> 01:13:42,719
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
 -I want you at my side 
 where you belong.

1215
01:13:42,752 --> 01:13:44,988
As the annual report 
 tells you, it has 
 been an exciting

1216
01:13:45,021 --> 01:13:47,457
and promising year. 
 Mitch.

1217
01:13:47,491 --> 01:13:50,760
Our presentation this year 
 holds considerable 
 significance.

1218
01:13:50,794 --> 01:13:53,530
We've made some 
 groundbreaking discoveries,

1219
01:13:53,563 --> 01:13:56,199
we've pioneered some 
 exciting new applications,

1220
01:13:56,232 --> 01:13:59,068
but of course, we couldn't 
 have done it alone.

1221
01:13:59,102 --> 01:14:01,104
-(CHIMPS CHATTERING)
 -Linda, would you bring 
 them out here.

1222
01:14:02,839 --> 01:14:04,941
-(CHIMP SCREECHING)
-You're next.

1223
01:14:07,644 --> 01:14:10,013
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING
AND CHEERING)

1224
01:14:11,080 --> 01:14:13,182
This is Laverne and Shirley.

1225
01:14:13,216 --> 01:14:15,985
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

1226
01:14:16,019 --> 01:14:19,589
As members of the species 
 evolutionarily closest 
 to humans,

1227
01:14:19,623 --> 01:14:21,958
they share 98% of our genes.

1228
01:14:21,991 --> 01:14:25,061
Their contribution to our 
 research has been invaluable.

1229
01:14:25,094 --> 01:14:26,863
As result of our work 
 with them,

1230
01:14:26,896 --> 01:14:28,932
a very special person

1231
01:14:28,965 --> 01:14:30,800
represents the Conlon 
 Institute tonight.

1232
01:14:30,834 --> 01:14:31,868
Good luck.

1233
01:14:32,969 --> 01:14:36,640
Ladies and gentlemen, 
 Miss Dina Blake.

1234
01:14:36,673 --> 01:14:38,074
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)
-(SIGHS)

1235
01:14:46,750 --> 01:14:48,652
Well, girls, it's past 
 your bedtime

1236
01:14:48,685 --> 01:14:51,187
-(CHIMPS SHRIEKING)
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

1237
01:14:54,591 --> 01:14:55,925
When we first met Dina,

1238
01:14:55,959 --> 01:14:58,061
she was far from the person 
 that we see here tonight.

1239
01:15:00,830 --> 01:15:04,033
Her mental capacity 
 was that of a kindergartner.

1240
01:15:04,067 --> 01:15:06,936
We put Dina 
 on the same formula schedule 
 as our chimps

1241
01:15:06,970 --> 01:15:08,638
and then we instituted 
 the same learning regimen

1242
01:15:08,672 --> 01:15:11,808
to see if she could achieve 
 the same level 
 of cognitive function.

1243
01:15:11,841 --> 01:15:13,743
MITCH: She did, and then some.

1244
01:15:13,777 --> 01:15:17,080
At our last evaluation, 
 Dina's IQ was placed at 172.

1245
01:15:17,747 --> 01:15:19,148
She's a genius.

1246
01:15:19,182 --> 01:15:21,585
Ladies and gentlemen, 
 Miss Dina Blake.

1247
01:15:21,618 --> 01:15:23,186
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

1248
01:15:29,258 --> 01:15:31,661
Who would have believed 
 it possible?

1249
01:15:32,929 --> 01:15:35,298
Take a strand of DNA,

1250
01:15:35,331 --> 01:15:37,901
a genetic messenger 
 that is tissue-specific,

1251
01:15:37,934 --> 01:15:39,569
and tell it to 
 go to the brain,

1252
01:15:39,603 --> 01:15:41,370
and it does.

1253
01:15:41,404 --> 01:15:44,941
It breaks through the barrier 
 between the brain 
 and the blood system,

1254
01:15:44,974 --> 01:15:47,611
something that has never been 
 done before, by the way.

1255
01:15:49,045 --> 01:15:52,248
These brilliant scientists

1256
01:15:52,281 --> 01:15:55,084
who stand before you,

1257
01:15:55,118 --> 01:15:58,287
-asking for your dollars 
 and cents, I might add... 
-(CROWD LAUGHING)

1258
01:15:58,321 --> 01:16:00,189
...have made history.

1259
01:16:00,223 --> 01:16:04,594
They've reached 
 into the brain cell itself

1260
01:16:04,628 --> 01:16:06,162
and they transformed it,

1261
01:16:06,896 --> 01:16:08,164
and they created

1262
01:16:09,799 --> 01:16:10,867
me.

1263
01:16:13,402 --> 01:16:18,908
The ramifications for 
 the future of genetic therapy 
 are staggering.

1264
01:16:18,942 --> 01:16:21,177
Once, I lived in a world 
 where I couldn't express

1265
01:16:22,178 --> 01:16:23,246
how I felt,

1266
01:16:25,815 --> 01:16:27,116
but I did.

1267
01:16:28,652 --> 01:16:29,318
Look.

1268
01:16:38,995 --> 01:16:41,197
And when they found me,

1269
01:16:41,230 --> 01:16:42,866
I knew I wanted something,

